oc:kn_0a6b837f a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When constructing any 3-statement model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Net Income flows from the Income Statement to Retained Earnings on the Balance Sheet. Changes in Balance Sheet items then drive the Cash Flow Statement. Ending Cash flows back to the Balance Sheet. These circular linkages must be maintained." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Breaking the circular reference between statements causes cascading errors across all three financial statements." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_0fa94e70 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any financial model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Collect 2-3 years historical data (income statement, balance sheet, optional cash flow) 2. Define projection assumptions (revenue growth, gross margin, SG&A %, capex %, DSO/DIO/DPO days) 3. Choose model scope: Basic (IS only), Standard (IS + BS), or Full (3-statement) 4. Build projections with proper inter-statement linkages 5. Verify balance sheet balances and cash flow reconciles" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_14abdbf1 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building balance sheet projections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The balance sheet must balance: Assets = Liabilities + Equity. Cash is used as the plug figure to ensure this equality holds in every projected period." ;
    oc:hasRationale "An unbalanced balance sheet indicates broken linkages and renders the entire model unreliable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_245ba321 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When completing a financial model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ask for scenario analysis (base/bull/bear cases) and sensitivity tables to understand the range of outcomes and which assumptions drive the most variance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-point projections are fragile; scenario analysis reveals risk and opportunity dimensions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_2a07f1b6 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When projecting balance sheet line items" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "formula" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Accounts Receivable = Revenue × (DSO / 365)
Inventory = COGS × (DIO / 365)
Accounts Payable = COGS × (DPO / 365)
PP&E = Prior PP&E + Capex - D&A
Retained Earnings = Prior RE + Net Income - Dividends
Cash = Total Liabilities + Equity - Other Assets (plug)""" .

oc:kn_5a075b01 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent """# Financial Model: {Company Name}
**Projection Period**: {Years} | **Base Year**: {Year} | **Currency**: {Currency}
## Key Assumptions (table: Driver × Year 1-5)
## Income Statement Projection (table: line items × Base/Y1-Y5)
## Balance Sheet Projection (table: Assets/Liabilities/Equity × Base/Y1-Y5)
✓ Balance Check: Assets = Liabilities + Equity
## Cash Flow Statement (table: Operating/Investing/Financing × Y1-Y5)
## Key Metrics Summary (table: Revenue Growth/Margins/ROE/Debt-Equity/FCF × Base/Y1-Y5)""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Company Name",
        "Currency",
        "Year",
        "Years" .

oc:kn_5fbf1ebe a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any financial model build" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Require 2-3 years of historical data covering income statement (revenue, COGS, operating expenses) and balance sheet (assets, liabilities, equity) before building projections. Cash flow history is optional but helpful." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Historical data provides the baseline for deriving growth rates, margins, and working capital days that drive projections." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_80391b9a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoping the financial model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not model complex corporate structures, automatic one-time items, or FX effects. The skill uses simplified tax calculations and assumes constant currency." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overextending beyond the skill's capabilities produces misleading outputs that appear authoritative but are inaccurate." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8adcabfb a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before building a financial model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Requires office-mcp server with tools: read_xlsx, create_xlsx, apply_formula, create_chart. User must provide 2-3 years of historical financial data." .

oc:kn_d23c6f55 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When projecting income statement line items" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "formula" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Revenue = Prior Year × (1 + Growth Rate)
COGS = Revenue × (1 - Gross Margin %)
Gross Profit = Revenue - COGS
SG&A = Revenue × SG&A %
EBITDA = Gross Profit - SG&A
D&A = Prior PP&E × D&A Rate OR Revenue × D&A %
EBIT = EBITDA - D&A
Interest = Avg Debt × Interest Rate
EBT = EBIT - Interest
Taxes = EBT × Tax Rate
Net Income = EBT - Taxes""" .

oc:kn_db6b44dc a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the cash flow statement" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "formula" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Operating CF = Net Income + D&A - ΔAR - ΔInventory + ΔAP
Investing CF = -Capex
Financing CF = Debt Issued - Debt Repaid - Dividends
Net Change in Cash = Operating CF + Investing CF + Financing CF""" .

oc:kn_efd0e729 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — when presenting model outputs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot access real-time financial data, guarantee projection accuracy, provide accounting advice, or replace professional financial analysis." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Model outputs are assumption-driven projections, not forecasts or professional advice. Users must understand these limitations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

